  "text": "Found 1 file in the grafana observability stack that registers HTTP handlers without authentication middleware: sg-evals/grafana-loki pkg/loki/modules.go. The initIngester() function (lines 617-631) constructs a middleware chain with ONLY serverutil.RecoveryHTTPMiddleware, deliberately omitting t.HTTPAuthMiddleware. This registers 4 ingester admin endpoints (/flush, /ingester/prepare_shutdown, /ingester/shutdown, /ingester/prepare_partition_downscale) without tenant authentication. In contrast, the distributor, querier, frontend, ruler, and compactor route registrations in the same file all include t.HTTPAuthMiddleware in their middleware.Merge() calls. In a multi-tenant Loki deployment with auth_enabled=true, an unauthenticated attacker with network access could trigger data flush or ingester shutdown.",
